FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - ZAMBIA: (NORTHERN)
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 24 Nov 2010
Source: OIE [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=9970>


Information received on [and dated] 24 Nov 2010 from Mr Moto Peter Crispin
Mangani, director, Veterinary and Livestock Development, Ministry of
Agriculture and Cooperatives, LUSAKA, Zambia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 22 Sep 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 3 Nov 2010
Report date: 24 Nov 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 24 Nov 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: December 2009
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Chizombwe, Mbala Central, Mbala, Northern
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Sep 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2920 / 72 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: the affected population is along the border with
Tanzania, where the disease is reported to be present.

Summary of outbreaks: total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case
fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 2.47 per cent / 0 per cent / 0 per cent / 0 per cent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or
slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection
- introduction of new live animals
- illegal movement of animals
- contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering

Control measures:
Measures applied
- quarantine
- movement control inside the country
- no vaccination
- no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied:
- vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Botswana Vaccine Institute (OIE's Reference
Laboratory)
Tests and results:
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / virus isolation / 3 Nov 2010 / Positive

Future Reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations: [see OIE website]

